# Java Comment Style

## Scope
All `.java` files.

## Rules

1. Single-line comments must use `//`.

2. Documentation or multi-line comments must use `///`.

3. Do NOT use traditional Javadoc block comments (`/** ... */`).

4. Each line of a documentation comment must start with `///`.

5. Comments should preferably be written in English.

6. For long documentation comments that require formatting, use **Markdown syntax**. Do not use HTML tags inside comments.

## Examples

### Single-line comment

// Calculate total price
int total = price * count;

### Documentation comment

/// Returns the user by ID
///
/// @param id user identifier
/// @return user entity
User getUser(Long id);

### Documentation comment with Markdown

/// Returns repository information
///
/// **Features**
/// - Supports pagination
/// - Supports filtering
/// - Supports sorting
///
/// @param query search query
/// @return paginated result

### Forbidden style

/**
 * Returns the user by ID
 */
User getUser(Long id);

### Forbidden formatting

/// <b>Repository information</b>
/// <ul>
///   <li>Pagination</li>
///   <li>Filtering</li>
/// </ul>